Mauritian Exports Rise 11% in 2010 on Increased Sales to U.S.,South Africa

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-24T07:15:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/mauritian-exports-rise-11-in-2010-on-increased-sales-to-u-s-south-africa.html
Mauritius’s total exports rose 11
percent in 2010 as demand for goods in the U.S. and  South Africa 
advanced, the  Central Statistics Office  said.  Total exports climbed to 39.8 billion rupees ($1.4 billion)
in 2010 compared with 36 billion rupees a year earlier, the Port
Louis-based agency said in a  statement  on its website today.  U.S imports of Mauritian goods rose 36 percent to 5.6
billion rupees, while exports to South Africa surged 47 percent
to 3.1 billion rupees.  Europe remains the country’s main market, led by France and
the U.K, which absorbed 69 percent of export-oriented
businesses’ output. Sales to the continent advanced 4.4 percent
to 27.6 billion rupees, the data agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
